name: lipid-A-disaccharide synthase
comment: Involved with EC 2.3.1.129 (acyl-[acyl-carrier-protein]---UDP-N-acetylglucosamine O-acyltransferase) and EC 2.7.1.130 (tetraacyldisaccharide 4'-kinase) in the biosynthesis of the phosphorylated glycolipid, lipid A, in the outer membrane of Escherichia coli.

references.title: The biosynthesis of gram-negative endotoxin. Formation of lipid A disaccharides from monosaccharide precursors in extracts of Escherichia coli.
Nucleotide sequence of the Escherichia coli gene for lipid A disaccharide synthase.
